import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['budgetYear'])]
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='budgetYear', color='blue')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of budgetYear?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    sns.boxplot(x=data['value'], color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['value'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['value'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of value?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x=data["abs_diff"], color="skyblue")
    ax.axvline(data["abs_diff"].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data["abs_diff"].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of abs_diff?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
